data.title: CHEAT SHEETS for any spontaneous politically-charged talk this Thanksgiving (I spent several hours making these! Hope SOMEONE finds them they helpful)
Message to the world recorded by Iranian university student shortly before he was "disappeared" by the Islamic Republic
I did one of the hardest things in my life today. I'm proud of myself.

images.description: A "family member" is a known abuser. At 30+ years old, I finally told my parents I wouldn't be here and neither will my daughters if he showed up. He's no longer coming and I think my mom is handling the backlash. I told my dad it's messed up that it's even an option for him to come. I'm done feeling like an 8 year old and my dad and husband support me 100%. My therapist is going to be proud of me too.

You can do hard things! I hope whomever reads this has the courage to stand up for what's right even if it "rocks the boat". Happy Holidays.

Viral Edit: Holy Crap Y'all! Thank you sooo much for the support and encouragement. You guys are amazing. I'm feeling so much more confident. Happiest of Holidays to all of you!!

data.title: Spotted Eagle Ray turns and passes right in front of my boat
data.description:
This is one of two Spotted Eagle Rays that were swimming over a very shallow grass bed. They were swimming alongside the boat for a short ways and then one of them turned and passed right in front of me. Spotted Eagle Rays are the second largest species of rays in the world after Manta Rays. Unlike Manta Rays, Spotted Eagle Rays have venomous barbs on their tails. 

All of the pics and videos I post are taken by me. For more OC (original content) nature vids check out my gallery at https://imgur.com/user/SeeThroughCanoe/posts

data.title: The murder victims of the club Q shooting

images.description:
Feel free to downvote my other post to upvote this one. I don't care about the points. This happened in my home town and it's devastating. These people didn't deserve to have their lives cut short. Their friends and family don't deserve the pain and anguish that can never be cured. This was senseless and horrifying.

I have two nephews who are trans and every time I see things like this or hear the hatred spewing from people's mouths, I fear for them. Why does someone's personal life evoke so much hate when it doesn't effect anyone else? Let them be themselves, let them have joy. 

I worry everytime my kids go to school. I'm hyper aware of my surroundings at work and in the grocery store. This is terrorism, and our country is full of it. I don't want this to be the world our kids grow up in.
